l feel for how others in the assassin comunity feel about our AF.<br>
<br>
If i am fighting the right mob thats yellow, but I have plusses to hit I have confidence I will win. yet I am beat all to pieces..again asit should be with a yellow. Then I find a good blue to fight. Still the same beat to pieces yet i won. Now get jumpes by a green and I do not have the plus to hit or damage and I die.  Whats wrong here? I have looked for blue con mobs to hunt all the time. Unless I find the best ones that I recieve the max bonus to hit they are very risky to hunt. The same can be said of a lot of greens.<br>
<br>
Yet once every few levels I find that priemum mob that my axe does massive damage to and i can solo yellows with ease. Something needs to be changed. I know I would love to be able to have confidence in killing any blue I run across and always have fear when I see yellows+.<br>
<br>
Personally I really feel our AF needs to be upped about 15-20% per leather type. I have a skald buddy that uses studded till 20 and he always has 100+ more af than I and that is the big difference between our melee survivability.<br>
<br>
Anyway just some rambling thoughts and I would like to know if any others here are doing AF/mob tests. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uciardhasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciardha Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 7:14:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2001.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/ciardha60a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: our armor</span><hr size=1> What level are you?  What does your armor con to you?  How's the quality on the armor?<br>
<br>
At 37, the only way a green's going to kill me is if I'm less than half health and no endurance, and even then I'd bet on me.  A blue will give me trouble if (a) I miss my opening shot and (b) get a string of never evading.  I can take the right yellows without any trouble (until I get the &quot;you will not evade me&quot; mob that kills me), yellows that get a bonus against leather tear me apart too fast.<br>
<br>
Most of my armor's high quality yellow/orange, with a single piece that I think just turned green and need to be upgraded. <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b>, Elven Nightshade<br>Guinevere<br><small>Explorer 93% | Killer 60% | Socializer 40% | Achiever 6%</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usirsameth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirSameth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 8:21:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2001.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: our armor</span><hr size=1> Morinn, what con armor/weapons do you have, and how did you spec? Having yellow gear is pretty much required for us to solo decently, orange makes things even easier. Also you may have some trouble if you spec really high in stealth. I heard that enerving poisons just got nerfed as well--if you are using those, that could be why you see a decrease in performance.<br>
<br>
I had the same problem as you...then I spend all my cash on some new gear (with a rockin' rapier from Mors on Galahad, thanks!) and after that I had no trouble.<br>
<br>
Other than that it could just be the mobs. I know that Cornish Hens were TOUGH for me as blues; the Moor Boogeys were same con and I think similar bonuses to hit, yet I could beat them easier...hope that helps.<br>
<br>
Sameth <br>
the 31st lvl Infiltrator<br>
Galahad<br>
